name: Mohamed Aymen Saied
content: Mohamed Aymen SAIED Mohamed Aymen SAIED Assistant Professor Laval University Office: 3955, Pavillon Adrien-Pouliot Tel: +1 (418) 656-2131 ext. 64810 Email: mohamed-aymen.saied@ift.ulaval.ca Website: aymen saied : @aymen_saied :Mohamed Aymen Saied I am an Assistant Professor at the Department of Computer Science and Software Engineering of Laval University. Prior to that, I was an Assistant Professor at the University of Quebec in Rimouski and an Affiliate Professor at Concordia University. From 2017 to 2018 I was a Post-Doctoral Fellow in the Electrical and Computer Engineering Department of Concordia University, as a member of the NSERC/Ericsson Industrial Research Chair on Model-Based Software Management. I received my Ph.D. in computer science from the University of Montreal, in 2016, as a member of the GEODES Software Engineering Research Group. In 2010 I graduated as an Engineer in Computer Science from the National School of Computer Science (Tunisia). I also obtained my Master of Science in Software Engineering and Business Intelligence from the same school in 2011, as a member of the Triskell Team, INRIA Rennes, (France). My research interests are at the intersection of software engineering, cloud-native systems, and software data analytics. Â© aymen saied All rights reserved.Design: Aymen
